cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI 

This paper addresses the Named Entity Disambiguation (NED) problem for short, user-generated texts on the social Web. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories such as Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a model of user-interest and Wikipedia to improve NED performance also suggests a focus on natural language processing and knowledge representation, which further supports the likelihood of cs.CL and cs.IR as potential sub-categories.
